track_description: Andromida is a one man metal project by composer and producer, Ramon Gutierrez. Diagnosed as legally blind at a young age, Ramon naturally felt a strong connection with music. He spent hours upon hours, days upon days, teaching himself how to arrange songs, produce, mix, and master his own music in his late high school years. During his time in college, Ramon began taking steps to start pursuing music. In 2016 the Andromida project was born.

track_title: Blood On My Hands (7 Sec - A) [No Vocals]
track_description: Incorporating a dynamic blend of instruments, the track features powerful guitars, thundering bass, relentless drums, and pulsating synthesizers, all expertly delivered. "Blood On My Hands" offers a high-octane musical experience like no other, serving as a testament to Beyond Unbroken's ability to captivate their audience while exploring the human experience and pushing the boundaries of Metal and Rock music.

Abandon all hope, Andromida and Daedric have come to deliver. Layered with powerful vocals courtesy of the one and only Daedric, "Abandon" is an emotionally turbulent ride from the get go. Andromida heavy thrashing guitars, ethereal synthesizers, and fast paced rhythms that round out a rock/orchestral mix. While provocative and thoughtful lyrics push through to the forefront like a shining centerpiece.

With Izzy Reign's debut full-length album with FiXT continuing the sound of her song 'Broken By Design', we've also brought along some exciting alt/rock tracks from her back catalog. Showcasing even more depth and artistry to this unique visionary, her track Extra! Extra! brings an infections blend of alt-rock and alt-pop.

Future rockers Fight The Fade are back with the driving new track "Scratching (feat. Daedric)". The track racks up the intensity from the start, featuring a combative vocal performance from both Zene Smith of Fight The Fade and Krystin Hope of Daedric, overlaid with thunderous rhythms and harsh guitar riffs.

"Closing In" blends the raw aggression of rock with synthesizers featured in today's metalcore. With fast paced rhythms, the song is a turbulent dive into the human psyche. The track captures the sensation of impending doom and the struggle against inner demons. With brutal vocal performances from both Coping Method's Tyler Simpson and the enigmatic REEBZ, the lyrics vividly portray the feeling of being trapped and pursued, with the protagonist grappling with paranoia and existential dread.

The Anix pulls you in with his latest alternative rock single, "Shadow." It isThe Anix's ability to blendmelancholic undertones and energetic instrumentation that truly bring this latest release to life. A master at emotive soundscapes, The Anix continues his exploration of the human condition in"Shadow."

"Hourglass" showcases ENMY's unique sound, characterized by soaring vocals, groove-oriented instrumentation, and electronic melodies. Standing out with its dynamic fusion of synth, guitar, bass, and drums, ENMY's "Hourglass" is a rich and layered soundscape that is both emotive and hard-hitting.
Hit the retro-future dancefloor with Fury Weekend's dance track "Feel The Beat", featuring PRIZM's lush vocalscreating a soundscape that is both nostalgic and refreshingly modern.
The Browning brings his signature blend of metal and electronic influences to his high energy riffs and beats with "Apollo".

Izzy Reign's song "Lite-Brite" draws from personal experiences of finding solace in music and colorful lights during tough isolated times. Blending the nostalgic sound of early 2000s techno with deep dark emotions, Reign creates a contrast between uplifting melodies and the hidden pain behind them.

track_title: The Anniversary Song On The Danube
track_description: An unexpected rendition of WAVES OF THE DANUBE, one of the most famous Romanian tunes in the world, beautifully played in an Eastern European folk fashion by the Cazanoi Bros. The emotional and sweet flute melody supported by the sensitively played cimbalom gets the best out of this beloved waltz. Subtle tempo shifts and melody dynamics imbue the track with a melancholic playfulness. Written by Iosif Ivanovici in 1880, the song made it into the Billboard charts on 1947, peaking at #2.
